Riedel Environment TechnologiesInc's subsidiary Riedel Environmental Services Inc &lt;RES>received a contract to clean up and remove hazardous substancesfrom contaminated sites in 23 states west of the MississippiRiver.    The contract, which could total more than 100 mln dlrs overthe next four years, is with the Federal EnvironmentalProtection Agency, the company said.    Among the states covered in the contract are Alaska andHawaii, as well as the Pacific Trust Territories, Riedel said. Reuter&#3;